\
1. Click on the Add A New Player button. Alternatively, click the load game button (the blue folder icon on the tool bar) and load the game with the file players.dat. \
\
2. Fill in the Player Name, Player ID, and Points fields. Click the Add Player button once you are done. \
\
3. Click the Start Game button to go back to the game tab. Select your player from the player area.\
\
4. Enter a bet into the bet field in the toolbar and click the poker chip button to place the bet. If the bet is valid, you will see a message in the status bar at the bottom of the frame and your player information will be updated in the player area to reflect your bet. \
\
5. Click the far right dice button on the tool bar to roll. This will roll for the selected player and then for the house once the player\'92s roll is over. \
\
6. After the house has finished rolling, the status bar will show the results of the game and the player\'92s new balance will be updated in the player area. \
